=====Usage notes=====
The choice between {{m|en|leapt}} and {{m|en|leaped}} is often generally a matter of regional differences: {{m|en|leapt}} is preferred in British English whereas {{m|en|leaped}} is somewhat more common in American English (although this is not to say that {{m|en|leapt}} is not used in American English, especially in areas with historical ties to England). According to research by John Algeo (''British or American English?'', Cambridge, 2006), {{m|en|leapt}} is used 80% of the time in UK and 32% in the US.

